---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About Belvedere Decks | Owner-Operated Deck Builder, Montgomery County MD"
  description="Belvedere Decks is an owner-operated composite deck company in Montgomery County, Maryland — code-first construction, transparent pricing, and a 10-year written workmanship warranty."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About us</p>
      <h1>A belvedere is a structure built to enjoy a beautiful view.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        That's what a deck is for — and it's the standard every project has to meet:
        something worth sitting on for the next twenty-five years.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Owner-operated, on purpose</h2>
      <p>
        When you call Belvedere Decks, you get the person who will measure your deck,
        price it in front of you, and stand behind it for the next decade. No sales rep
        who disappears after the contract, no rotating crews who've never seen your
        drawings. Owner-operated is slower to scale — and better to hire.
      </p>

      <h2>The code-nerd difference</h2>
      <p>
        We're the company that narrates your deck inspection out loud: the screwdriver
        test on your posts, the flashing check where the ledger meets your house, the
        joist spacing that determines whether composite boards will sag. If we find
        something that changes the scope, we show you and adjust together — before the
        contract, not after demo. Building code isn't a hurdle we clear; it's the floor
        we build up from.
      </p>

      <h2>What every project includes</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>An exact price presented in person — same visit for refloors and facelifts</li>
        <li>Three configurations, with the same code-perfect structure under all three</li>
        <li>Premium TimberTech and Trex boards, entry to architectural grade</li>
        <li>Permits and inspections handled where required</li>
        <li>A 10-year written workmanship warranty — on top of 25–50-year manufacturer board warranties</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where we work</h2>
      <p>
        We serve Montgomery County, Maryland — Potomac, North Potomac and the Kentlands,
        Bethesda, Olney, Boyds, and Clarksburg. Based in Potomac; building all around it.
      </p>
      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Get in touch</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
